Calculate logical AND between two pages.

Parameters:
page The page to scan, can be any size.
out Must be preallocated to the same size as page. All records in this page will be given a value or 0 or 1 based on the result of the comparison.
obj Must be EaglePage* which becomes the right operand for page to calculate logical AND against. This page must also be the same size (or greater) of page and out

Calculate values in a page that are greater than an integer.

This function does not allocate memory.

Parameters:
page The page to scan, can be any size.
out Must be preallocated to the same size as page. All records in this page will be given a value or 0 or 1 based on the result of the comparison.
obj Must be int* which is dereferenced to the integer value for comparison.
